org.firebirdsql.jca

Class FBResourceException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • javax.resource.ResourceException
          • org.firebirdsql.jca.FBResourceException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FBIncorrectXidException, FBResourceTransactionException

    public class FBResourceException
extends javax.resource.ResourceException
    FBResourceException should be used in places where ResourceException should be thrown according to the interface specification, but we do not want to lose the exception that we caught.

    Example: 

     try {
     // execute some code here
     ...
 } catch(GDSException gdsex) {
     throw new FBResourceException(gdsex);
 }

    Author:
    Roman Rokytskyy
